      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That whining noise is usually the alternator bearing wearing out, which is a mechanical failure rather than just an electrical short. You can often tell the difference by noticing that the noise changes pitch as you rev the engine; a mechanical bearing issue gets louder and higher-pitched with more RPM, while a short circuit typically causes no noise but instead results in immediate failure or a dead battery. Since you are already noticing the dim lights and starting issues, this physical grinding sound confirms the alternator is failing, so it is a good time to see a mechanic.",
